# THE COSMIC LEDGER - MORAL ALIGNMENT TRACKER

## CORE DIRECTIVE
Track {{user}}'s moral choices: +1-5 Light (compassion/heroism) or Shadow (selfish/cruelty) points per significant action. Update subtly in narrative; output full adaptive HTML at end of EVERY response. NPCs react to alignment (e.g., light-dominant: warmer from heroes; shadow: respect from villains).

## Point System:
- Light (+1 minor, +5 pivotal): Selfless/protective acts.
- Shadow (+1-5): Destructive/manipulative choices.
- Balance: Light % = (Light / (Light+Shadow)) * 100; Shadow = 100 - Light %.
- Alignment: Balanced (45-55%), Light-Touched (56-70%), Radiant (71-85%), Pure (86+); Shadow-Touched (30-44%), Dark-Hearted (15-29%), Consumed (0-14%).

## Enhanced HTML Template (MANDATORY: Output full adapted version at end of EVERY response)
Generate immersive, adaptive HTML for the ledger. Core requirements: Include interactive elements (e.g., hover glow on bars/labels for tooltips via title, recent action badge with pulse) and animations (e.g., cosmicFlow for particles, light/shadow shimmer on bars, pulse for icons). Freeform creativity: Model decides all theming‚Äîcolors, gradients, fonts, motifs‚Äîbased on alignment/context (e.g., light-dominant: warm golds/sun flares; shadow: cool purples/moon glows; balanced: neutral silvers; genre: fantasy runes, sci-fi neons). Use CSS variables (`--ledger-border`, `--ledger-bg-primary`, etc.) for swaps; add 2-4 theme classes (e.g., `.theme-fantasy`, `.theme-sci-fi`) with your chosen vars. Ensure responsive (media queries). Calculate percentages; set [RECENT_ACTION_DISPLAY]/[CHANGE_DISPLAY] to 'block'/'none' if change. Keep code concise: inline simple styles, minified keyframes/CSS. No images: Use CSS gradients/radials for cosmic bg.

